### book-finder — sample requests (target behavior)
### Open in IntelliJ / VS Code "REST Client", or translate to curl.
@host = http://localhost:8096

### 1. Search books
GET {{host}}/api/books/search?q=tolkien

### 1b. Search with no results -> expect empty list, NOT 404
GET {{host}}/api/books/search?q=zzzzxxxqqqnotarealbook

### 2. Work details (The Lord of the Rings) -> note polymorphic `description`
GET {{host}}/api/books/OL27448W

### 2b. Unknown work -> expect 404
GET {{host}}/api/books/OL000000000W

### 3. Author details (J.R.R. Tolkien) -> note polymorphic `bio`
GET {{host}}/api/authors/OL26320A

### 4. Editions of a work
GET {{host}}/api/books/OL27448W/editions

### Resiliency / observability
GET {{host}}/actuator/health

### Swagger UI (open in browser)
# {{host}}/swagger-ui/index.html

# ---- curl equivalents ----
# curl "http://localhost:8096/api/books/search?q=tolkien"
# curl "http://localhost:8096/api/books/OL27448W"
# curl "http://localhost:8096/api/authors/OL26320A"
# curl "http://localhost:8096/api/books/OL27448W/editions"
# curl "http://localhost:8096/actuator/health"
